*----------------------------------------------------------------------
* test/fence_function/t07_arbno_fence.sno
* Corpus idiom: ARBNO(ELEM FENCE) or ARBNO(ITEM FENCE)
* FENCE as 0-arg inside ARBNO: each ARBNO iteration commits, no
* retry of previous iterations.
* Also: ARBNO(FENCE(P)) - fence each iteration's match.
*
* From corpus/programs (expression.sno):
*   F3  =  ARBNO(ELEM FENCE)
*   PLI.STMT = POS(0) (ARBNO(ELEM FENCE) ';') . STMT
*----------------------------------------------------------------------

*   Simple ARBNO(word FENCE) — parse space-separated words, committed
               WS    = ' '
               word  = BREAK(' ' ) | REM
               S = 'one two three'
               count = 0
LP             S  (BREAK(' ') | REM) . w  FENCE              :F(DONE)
               count = count + 1
               S = S (SIZE(w) + 1)                           :(LP)  
DONE
*   Should have consumed first word then stopped (FENCE prevents retry)
*   Actually FENCE 0-arg here kills whole match on backtrack from outer
*   Let's do the FENCE(P) form instead:

               S2 = 'abc123def'
               digits = '0123456789'
               alpha  = 'abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyzABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ'
*   Match alternating alpha/digit runs with FENCE commitment
               S2  FENCE(SPAN(alpha) | SPAN(digits)) . tok   :F(FAIL7)
               OUTPUT = IDENT(tok, 'abc') 'PASS t07: FENCE(P) in sequence, got [' tok ']'
                                                             :(END)
FAIL7          OUTPUT = 'FAIL t07: FENCE(SPAN(alpha)|SPAN(digits)) on abc123def'
END
